<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6511/1250</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Swiss Legation</gloss> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi><note n="4" xml:id="d217fn4">Similar memorandum of the same date received
                                    from the Swiss Legation with respect to German
                                interests.</note></head>
                            <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi></p>
                            <p>Offering and warranting reciprocity the Italian Government would like
                                to see the departure of the staff of the Italian Embassy, including
                                all dependents, arranged under the following conditions: <list>
                                    <label>1.)</label>
                                    <item>Safe-conduct from an American to a European port.</item>
                                    <label>2.)</label>
                                    <item>Guarantees that the vessel bringing the staff back to
                                        Europe will not be forced to call at an inimical port or
                                        stopped at sea by enemy forces.</item>
                                    <label>3.)</label>
                                    <item>Illimited removal of personal belongings.</item>
                                    <label>4.)</label>
                                    <item>Exemption of control and search of any kind of the staff
                                        and the dependents as well as the private belongings taken
                                        along.</item>
                                    <label>5.)</label>
                                    <item>Guarantees against seizure of such belongings.</item>
                                </list></p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-13">December 13, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>